HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1151
By Vital
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Geraldine Tanner of
Chattanooga.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Geraldine Tanner of Chattanooga; and
WHEREAS, Geraldine Tanner was a beloved member of her community who worked
assiduously to improve the lives of her fellow citizens in numerous capacities; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Tanner was deeply devoted to her faith and was a longtime member of
Maple Grove Baptist Church; she found great joy in worship and serving others within her
church and community, and her life was a reflection of her deep and abiding faith; and
WHEREAS, Geraldine Tanner was an employee of Cutter Lab and later worked at 3M
as a plant nurse while attending nursing school; she served at several hospitals as a Registered
Nurse, including Siskin Hospital and Downtown General. She later provided compassionate
care through home health services; and
WHEREAS, nursing was more than just a career to Ms. Tanner—it was a ministry; she
touched countless lives with her kindness and steady presence before taking her much-
deserved retirement in 2005 after forty years of service to her community; and
WHEREAS, in addition to finding joy in her faith and her service to her community,
Geraldine Tanner was a proud member of the Chattanooga Porcelain Artists Guild, where she
expressed her artistic talents and showcased her love for porcelain art through her patience,
attention to detail, and appreciation for beauty; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Tanner will be remembered for her unwavering faith, her servant's
heart, and her creative spirit; and
WHEREAS, beyond her service to others, Geraldine Tanner found her greatest joy in
her family and friends, including her church family; and
HJR1151
015429
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Ms. Tanner is survived by her son, Dale Hixson; daughter-in-law, Susan
Hixson; several grandchildren, great-grandchildren, nieces, and nephews; and a host of friends
and church family; and
WHEREAS, she was preceded in death by her husband, Don Tanner; son, Tony Hixson;
daughters-in-law, Velma Hixson and Nancy Gold; father, Ben Davis; mother, Cydna Davis;
brothers, Burnice, H.M. "Buster," Sam, and Don; and sisters, Sara and Patricia; and
WHEREAS, Geraldine Tanner leaves behind an indelible legacy of integrity and probity
in public life, compassion and loyalty in private life, and diligence and dedication in all her
chosen endeavors; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
remember the bountiful life of this exceptional public servant and human being; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor the memory of Geraldine Tanner, reflecting fondly upon her
impeccable character and her stalwart commitment to living the examined life with courage and
conviction.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we express our sympathy and offer our condolences
to the family of Ms. Tanner.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
